Containers are used in modern solutions to build scalable, portable, and efficient applications.

They enable microservices architecture where each component runs independently.

For example, an application can have separate containers for frontend, backend, and database services.

A real-life use case is CI/CD pipelines where containers ensure consistent environments across development and production.

Another example is cloud-native applications designed to scale automatically.

Containers improve flexibility, deployment speed, and reliability.
